File search in your system.
===========================

   All needed for files and directories :


 @{" Directories " Link "Directories"} 
 @{" Magics " Link "Magics"} 

 @{" DEFAULTSEND " Link "DEFAULTSEND"} 
 @{" INDEXONLY " Link "INDEXONLY"} 


@EndNode

@Node "Directories" "FFRS.guide/Directories"
@Next "Magics"
@Toc "File search"

Directories of your system.
---------------------------

   @{b}*@{ub} Template: DIRECTORY <dir> [PASSWORD <password>] [FREE]

     Specifies one directory where to look for requested files (after
     checking magics). There can be as many DIRECTORY keywords as you
     like. (FFRI uses these for creating its index file. When the ,
     keyword INDEXONLY is used, these directories are not searched
     during the actual request if a file is not found in the index. See
     @{"INDEXONLY" Link "INDEXONLY"}.)

     When no password or the wrong password is given, not found or
     password error is displayed in the reportfile for the user, while
     you are informed in detail via your logfile.

     If you specify FREE, files requested from this directory are not
     affected by the request limit.

     Example:

     DIRECTORY FILE:25/
     DIRECTORY 'UDBase0:fido software'
     DIRECTORY FILE:Secret PASSWORD none_knows


@EndNode

